[6] Colombia (Barranquilla)
Date: 31 Aug 2011
Source: Fuente: El Heraldo, Colombia [in Spanish, trans. Mod.JT,
edited]
http://www.elheraldo.co/local/distrito-refuerza-vacunaci-n-contra-sarampi-n-tras-confirmarse-otros-dos-casos-35860



The Health Secretariat of Barranquilla confirmed that the 2 new
measles cases in the district are a 46 year old and a boy of 5 years,
both relatives of a teenager who was in Brazil and who was recently
confirmed as the 1st case of the disease in the country.

After these new cases, epidemiological surveillance of measles was
strengthened, especially among tourists and travelers coming to
Ernesto Cortissoz International Airport, and was also enhanced in the
city.

"We will boost prevention efforts with several actions. One is the
installation of a vaccination and information centre at Ernesto
Cortissoz International Airport, and we will require tourists and
travelers, who carry vaccination cards, to verify they have been
immunized," said secretary of the health district, Martha Rodriguez
Otalora.

The emergency plan of action continues with implementation of the
measles-rubella vaccine to vulnerable people in the city -- that is,
children and young people aged between 11 and 19 years, and people who
are traveling abroad. In the same way, advanced educational
institutions, children's homes, shopping centres, churches, and
businesses will be included if they request it.

Between 11 to 27 Aug 2011, intensified efforts will be made to
vaccinate the entire population of Barranquilla.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-ESP <promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the ProMED-ESP moderator, the index case confirmed by
health authorities 6 days ago in the city of Barranquilla was a 15
year old who had been in Brazil recently. Since 2002, there had been
[no] outbreak of measles in Colombia.

Barranquilla is an industrial port city and municipality located in
northern Colombia, near the Caribbean Sea. It has a population of 1
148 506 (as of 2005), and it can be located in the map of Colombia at
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barranquilla. - Mod.CP]

