[9] New Zealand (Auckland)
Date: Tue 30 Aug 2011
Source: Voxy News Engine [abridged & edited]
http://www.voxy.co.nz/health/117-confirmed-cases-measles-auckland/5/99860


The Auckland Regional Public Health Service can confirm 117 cases of
measles in the Auckland region as of this morning [30 Aug 2011]. Two
contacts are in quarantine. Nine cases have required hospitalisation
during this outbreak. Most cases have occurred in West Auckland with
some spread to Central Auckland, North Shore, and Manuka.

The measles outbreak is now into its 3rd month. Medical Officer of
Health Dr Richard Hoskins is urging the following people to please
contact their doctor to check their immunity status: Those who were
present in the waiting room of the Middlemore Hospital Coronary Care
Unit on Tue 23 Aug 2011 between 4:00 and 7:00 pm, and who were born
after January 1969, and who have not been fully immunised (received 2
measles vaccines). "There was a child with measles in the waiting room
during this time, so it's important that those people who fit the
criteria outlined above contact their doctor. They could possibly
develop the disease over the next week," says Dr Hoskins.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of confirmed cases of measles has increased from 111 on 22
Aug 2011 to the present 117.

The number of reports of measles outbreaks may be beginning to
decline, hopefully as a consequence of the increasing awareness of the
need to achieve high levels of vaccine uptake. Reports of the
situation in Asian countries continue to be sparse. - Mod.CP]
